marked: Posterior cortical atrophy (PCA)
Neuropathological studies demonstrated that the primary cause of PCA is Alzheimer’s disease followed, more rarely, by corticobasal degeneration, dementia with Lewy bodies or prion disease
Therefore, we aimed first to use brain SPECT to study the profile of brain hypoperfusion in a large group of patients with PCA, compared with normal controls and patients with Alzheimer’s disease.
